01:38:18.758 --> 01:38:20.448
Nobody ever goes deep inside.

01:38:43.137 --> 01:38:46.586
- It wasn't what you
did, it was how easy

01:38:47.655 --> 01:38:48.689
we got away with it.

01:38:53.137 --> 01:38:55.034
You carried on as
if nothing happened.

01:38:58.172 --> 01:38:59.896
I couldn't do that.

01:39:07.551 --> 01:39:08.931
I had to try it again.

01:39:10.551 --> 01:39:12.310
- Right, let's go.

01:39:12.310 --> 01:39:14.896
- Pick someone at
random, a stranger.

01:39:16.482 --> 01:39:19.413
It became my hobby,
my pet project.

01:39:22.034 --> 01:39:24.000
And then you came back.

01:39:29.000 --> 01:39:31.413
And now you know too much.

01:40:17.896 --> 01:40:19.793
Good morning, could
I please have a taxi?

01:40:19.793 --> 01:40:21.275
- When for?

01:40:21.275 --> 01:40:22.448
- Yes, for now.

01:40:22.448 --> 01:40:23.931
What's the address?

01:40:23.931 --> 01:40:26.068
- It's one, two,
seven Renton Street.

01:40:26.068 --> 01:40:26.931
- The name?

01:40:26.931 --> 01:40:28.137
- Yeah, Cleek.

01:40:28.137 --> 01:40:29.068
- Okay
as soon as we can.

01:40:29.068 --> 01:40:30.000
- Okay, thank you.

01:40:48.172 --> 01:40:50.034
Good morning Russell.

01:40:50.034 --> 01:40:50.862
- Morning.

01:40:55.000 --> 01:40:56.344
I was here a few hours ago.

01:40:58.275 --> 01:40:59.655
That girl said you were out.

01:41:03.034 --> 01:41:05.758
- Yes, Norma did say
you were looking for me,

01:41:05.758 --> 01:41:06.793
hence the phone call.

01:41:06.793 --> 01:41:08.517
- Where is she this Norma girl?

01:41:09.620 --> 01:41:10.689
Did she mention Christine?

01:41:10.689 --> 01:41:12.206
- Christine?

01:41:12.206 --> 01:41:14.206
I'm afraid not.

01:41:14.206 --> 01:41:17.103
Norma's way back to
Ireland some bother

01:41:17.103 --> 01:41:18.517
with an ex-junkie boyfriend.

01:41:19.689 --> 01:41:21.896
- Is she another one of
your distant friends?

01:41:23.827 --> 01:41:25.137
- Russell, why do I
get the impression

01:41:25.137 --> 01:41:27.034
you're not here to
talk about Norma, hmm?

01:41:27.034 --> 01:41:30.172
- Because you arranged to
meet Christine last night,

01:41:30.172 --> 01:41:32.655
and now nobody can
get ahold of her.

01:41:32.655 --> 01:41:35.517
That's strange don't
you think considering

01:41:35.517 --> 01:41:37.275
you were out all night?

01:41:37.275 --> 01:41:39.448
- It is strange.

01:41:39.448 --> 01:41:41.620
And that's what I thought
when she didn't show up.

01:41:43.000 --> 01:41:45.827
As for me being out all
night, after our conversation

01:41:45.827 --> 01:41:48.103
I took a shift at the
pub, and then I met

01:41:48.103 --> 01:41:50.896
up with a friend,
and I'm afraid to say

01:41:50.896 --> 01:41:53.206
it got rather messy.

01:41:54.551 --> 01:41:56.655
- And your friend,
what's his name?

01:41:56.655 --> 01:41:58.103
- Sam McBride.

01:41:58.103 --> 01:42:01.620
- This Sam, he'll be
able to corroborate this?

01:42:03.068 --> 01:42:03.931
- Corroborate?

01:42:05.310 --> 01:42:07.931
Yeah, he'll be able
to corroborate it

01:42:07.931 --> 01:42:09.310
if you can get ahold of him.

01:42:10.448 --> 01:42:12.310
You see Sam and Norma
became very close,

01:42:13.655 --> 01:42:17.862
so he left with her to
protect her from this junkie.

01:42:20.000 --> 01:42:22.620
And I think it's time I
found myself a new sponsor

01:42:24.551 --> 01:42:27.034
'cause I've had quite
enough of these harassments.

01:42:28.586 --> 01:42:31.344
Now if you'll excuse me?

01:42:55.517 --> 01:42:56.689
Shush.

01:42:57.827 --> 01:42:59.827
Shush.

01:43:02.206 --> 01:43:03.965
I wish I could make
it more humane.

01:43:05.655 --> 01:43:06.482
Don't worry.

01:43:07.379 --> 01:43:08.379
They will find you.

01:43:10.103 --> 01:43:13.103
You will be my last
ever victim here,

01:43:13.103 --> 01:43:14.827
and the only one
ever to be found.

01:43:16.172 --> 01:43:17.827
I truly am sorry.

01:43:57.103 --> 01:43:58.206
Good morning Susan.

01:43:58.206 --> 01:43:59.310
- Morning.

01:43:59.310 --> 01:44:00.137
- Running late today?

01:44:00.137 --> 01:44:00.965
- Just a little.

01:44:05.482 --> 01:44:08.344
Jacob, I was wondering if
you'd like to go out sometime

01:44:09.448 --> 01:44:12.724
for a coffee,
lunch, even dinner.

01:44:12.724 --> 01:44:14.586
- Are you free Tuesday nights?

01:44:14.586 --> 01:44:16.517
- Afraid not, I work
late on a Tuesday.

01:44:18.689 --> 01:44:19.758
Why Tuesdays?

01:44:20.758 --> 01:44:21.586
- No reason.

01:44:23.000 --> 01:44:24.310
Isn't that your bus coming?

01:44:33.517 --> 01:44:35.172
How 'bout Wednesday?

01:45:10.310 --> 01:45:11.931
- What you reading?

01:45:13.517 --> 01:45:15.000
- Do you remember that
woman who was killed

01:45:15.000 --> 01:45:17.034
in an alley the week before
we went on our first date?

01:45:18.551 --> 01:45:19.379
- Vaguely.

01:45:23.310 --> 01:45:26.379
- Well it seems that
a tissue containing

01:45:26.379 --> 01:45:28.655
her saliva was found
in a self storage park

01:45:28.655 --> 01:45:30.379
along with several other bodies.

01:45:30.379 --> 01:45:31.620
What did you see?

01:45:31.620 --> 01:45:33.034
It says that on the
tissue there were

01:45:33.034 --> 01:45:34.862
specks of blood from a
mechanic named Richard Foster,

01:45:34.862 --> 01:45:37.172
and he's the main suspect.

01:45:37.172 --> 01:45:39.000
The self storage
container was opened

01:45:39.000 --> 01:45:40.620
when the rent on the
property hadn't been paid

01:45:40.620 --> 01:45:42.034
for several months.

01:45:42.034 --> 01:45:44.310
The tenant paid in
cash, and police believe

01:45:44.310 --> 01:45:47.758
the name used Gary Lutz is
fake, and there might be

01:45:47.758 --> 01:45:51.517
a serial killer or
killers targeting women.

01:45:53.379 --> 01:45:54.896
- Why are you so interested?

01:45:57.103 --> 01:45:58.000
- It's just scary.

01:46:00.379 --> 01:46:01.724
You could've been a victim.

01:46:04.379 --> 01:46:06.793
- Well I'm just glad
we moved to the country

01:46:06.793 --> 01:46:08.206
where it's safe.

01:46:09.758 --> 01:46:11.275
I'll go fix us some lunch, hey?

01:46:34.551 --> 01:46:36.724
Jacob, that's lunch ready.

01:46:39.931 --> 01:46:42.000
There's actually something
else I kinda wanted

01:46:42.000 --> 01:46:43.931
to talk to you about.

01:46:43.931 --> 01:46:47.241
It ties in with living
in a safe place.

01:46:47.241 --> 01:46:49.172
- I look forward to it.

01:46:50.310 --> 01:46:53.517
- Anyway,
I'll make up some tea.

01:46:57.172 --> 01:47:01.931
- I believe the next few months
will be very interesting.

